00:35:02,667 --> 00:35:04,602
[♪♪♪]

736
00:35:05,636 --> 00:35:07,705
ANGELO:
Sometimes I think

737
00:35:07,772 --> 00:35:11,876
if I've gotta listen to these
voices for one more second,

738
00:35:11,943 --> 00:35:14,846
I swear to God...

739
00:35:14,912 --> 00:35:16,447
[SIGHS]

740
00:35:16,514 --> 00:35:20,418
That was the first time
I ever saw a gun up close.

741
00:35:23,354 --> 00:35:24,989
And Dad...

742
00:35:25,056 --> 00:35:27,158
makin' out like he was...

743
00:35:27,225 --> 00:35:30,161
some kind of a bandit.

744
00:35:30,228 --> 00:35:32,497
And Mom, oh.

745
00:35:32,563 --> 00:35:35,433
She just about had a fit.

746
00:35:37,735 --> 00:35:40,905
"Put it away, put it away."

747
00:35:47,278 --> 00:35:49,280
Mom.

748
00:35:49,347 --> 00:35:51,315
[SIGHS]

749
00:35:54,619 --> 00:35:56,921
Hey, Ange.

750
00:35:56,988 --> 00:35:59,056
Huh?
We're here.

751
00:35:59,123 --> 00:36:01,492
Oh, yeah, sorry.

752
00:36:09,834 --> 00:36:13,638
Rudy.
Oh, yes. Over here, come on.

753
00:36:13,704 --> 00:36:16,340
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]
Take a walk.

754
00:36:17,642 --> 00:36:20,211
Hey, Tony,
what are you doin'?

755
00:36:22,313 --> 00:36:24,048
Uh, hello, Mary.
[DOG GROWLS]

756
00:36:24,115 --> 00:36:25,783
What do you want?

757
00:36:25,850 --> 00:36:27,518
Well, I-I need to talk
to your husband.

758
00:36:27,585 --> 00:36:29,754
Is Charlie here?
No!

759
00:36:29,820 --> 00:36:31,956
Uh, are you,
uh, expecting him?

760
00:36:32,023 --> 00:36:34,091
You think I'm gonna
tell you where he is?

761
00:36:34,158 --> 00:36:36,060
Look, I, uh, I know what
I said earlier--

762
00:36:36,127 --> 00:36:37,428
Oh, great.
No, I just--

763
00:36:37,495 --> 00:36:39,830
Could I just come in
for second? Just a second?

764
00:36:39,897 --> 00:36:41,532
[SIGHS]

765
00:36:41,599 --> 00:36:43,668
You got a lot of fuckin' nerve,
you know that?

766
00:36:43,734 --> 00:36:44,802
Mary, please.

767
00:36:44,869 --> 00:36:46,504
You wanna do somethin'
to him, right?

768
00:36:46,571 --> 00:36:47,939
No!
Bullshit!

769
00:36:48,005 --> 00:36:49,907
I'm in a jam here.
It's a different situation

770
00:36:49,974 --> 00:36:51,876
from this morning.
What do you want him for?

771
00:36:51,943 --> 00:36:54,111
I just wanna talk to him.
It's a business thing.

772
00:36:54,178 --> 00:36:55,913
Liar!
I am not lyin'.

773
00:36:55,980 --> 00:36:57,848
Honest to God,
on a stack of bibles.

774
00:36:57,915 --> 00:36:59,517
You gonna tell me
where he's at?

775
00:36:59,584 --> 00:37:01,886
You gonna tell me when
you're expecting him?

776
00:37:01,953 --> 00:37:03,554
Are you expecting him?

777
00:37:03,621 --> 00:37:06,223
Are you not living together
anymore? Are you separated?

778
00:37:06,290 --> 00:37:08,059
I'm not tellin'!

779
00:37:08,125 --> 00:37:10,828
Look, I don't wanna fight with
you anymore, 'cause you're upset

780
00:37:10,895 --> 00:37:13,030
about what happened earlier
today. Okay, I'm sorry.

781
00:37:13,097 --> 00:37:15,633
I had a bad morning. Mary,
I am running out of time here.

782
00:37:15,700 --> 00:37:19,203
All I'm asking is where is your
husband? It's a simple thing.

783
00:37:19,270 --> 00:37:21,238
You're acting as if
I'm gonna shoot him!

784
00:37:21,305 --> 00:37:22,907
I swear to you,
that's not the case.

785
00:37:22,974 --> 00:37:25,910
I-I give you my word.

786
00:37:25,977 --> 00:37:29,080
If I tell you,
what'll you give me?

787
00:37:29,146 --> 00:37:31,349
Whatever you want.

788
00:37:31,415 --> 00:37:33,985
Whatever I want?

789
00:37:34,051 --> 00:37:35,987
Yeah.

790
00:37:36,053 --> 00:37:37,188
What do you want?

791
00:37:37,254 --> 00:37:40,324
[SIGHS]

792
00:37:40,391 --> 00:37:41,859
Money.

793
00:37:46,831 --> 00:37:49,233
Money?

794
00:37:49,300 --> 00:37:53,604
You want me
to give you money?

795
00:37:53,671 --> 00:37:55,773
Yeah.

796
00:37:59,844 --> 00:38:01,512
[SIGHS]

797
00:38:01,579 --> 00:38:04,382
You're
a piece of work.

798
00:38:04,448 --> 00:38:07,418
Oh, yeah.

799
00:38:08,519 --> 00:38:10,321
Uh, hey.
Hey! Hey!

800
00:38:10,388 --> 00:38:13,524
TONY:
Rudy, I get the feeling that
Ange knows this dame. Ya know?

801
00:38:13,591 --> 00:38:15,393
Think so?
Yeah.

802
00:38:15,459 --> 00:38:17,061
No. No, way.

803
00:38:17,128 --> 00:38:18,729
And, and? Huh?
Come on.

804
00:38:18,796 --> 00:38:21,065
Pleasantville Hospital.
He's in the hospital?

805
00:38:21,132 --> 00:38:22,600
Yeah.
Hey, Mary,

806
00:38:22,667 --> 00:38:24,802
is it okay if I put on this--?
Get the hell out of here!

807
00:38:24,869 --> 00:38:27,505
You heard him. Get outta here.
Wait a minute. Who was that?

808
00:38:27,571 --> 00:38:30,274
Was that a guy?
That was a guy!

809
00:38:30,341 --> 00:38:31,776
What the fuck
is the matter with you?

810
00:38:31,842 --> 00:38:34,612
I don't like bein' alone, okay?
I guess not.

811
00:38:34,679 --> 00:38:36,847
What do you know, anyway?
Why don't you get outta here?

812
00:38:36,914 --> 00:38:38,749
You got what you wanted.
That ain't right.

813
00:38:38,816 --> 00:38:40,484
You don't know anything
about right.

814
00:38:40,551 --> 00:38:42,720
You're a goddamn thug!
Thug? What do you mean, thug?

815
00:38:42,787 --> 00:38:45,089
What are you
beatin' on me for?

816
00:38:45,156 --> 00:38:47,091
[INDISTINCT TAUNTING]

817
00:38:47,158 --> 00:38:49,694
[BOTH GRUNTING]

818
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:52,363
[GASPS THEN SCREAMS]
[THUDS]

819
00:38:52,430 --> 00:38:55,332
MARY:
You cut people's heads off
and you point a finger at me?

820
00:38:55,399 --> 00:38:57,168
ANGELO:
Are you nuts? What head?

821
00:38:57,234 --> 00:38:58,769
You know what
I'm talking about.

822
00:38:58,836 --> 00:39:00,571
You can't talk to me that way.
Oh, yeah?

823
00:39:00,638 --> 00:39:02,907
Who's gonna stop me, you?
Yeah, me. And I got four guys

824
00:39:02,973 --> 00:39:05,443
waitin' outside who'd happily
break your friggin' neck

825
00:39:05,509 --> 00:39:07,278
if I asked them.
So don't start with this--

826
00:39:07,345 --> 00:39:08,813
Oh, shut up.
Oh, shut up, huh?

827
00:39:08,879 --> 00:39:11,415
Okay, have it your way.
I'm sick of your mentality.

828
00:39:11,482 --> 00:39:13,150
I don't why you're so
goddamn mean to me.

829
00:39:13,217 --> 00:39:15,052
What did I ever do to you?
I'm a good person.

830
00:39:15,119 --> 00:39:16,887
Your husband's lying sick
in the hospital

831
00:39:16,954 --> 00:39:18,923
and you're screwin' half
of the friggin' city!

832
00:39:18,989 --> 00:39:21,492
What do you think
he's in there for, appendicitis?

833
00:39:21,559 --> 00:39:24,261
It's a mental hospital.

834
00:39:24,328 --> 00:39:27,098
[♪♪♪]

835
00:39:27,164 --> 00:39:28,933
It is?

836
00:39:32,136 --> 00:39:35,406
He's been committed.
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

837
00:39:35,473 --> 00:39:38,209
He is?
Yeah.

838
00:39:38,275 --> 00:39:39,777
Since when?

839
00:39:39,844 --> 00:39:43,047
Oh, I don't know,
a couple of weeks ago.

840
00:39:43,114 --> 00:39:46,617
He just kept gettin'
worse and worse.

841
00:39:46,684 --> 00:39:49,253
Uh, gee, Mary, uh, I'm sorry.
Uh, I didn't know.

842
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:50,688
I couldn't
take it anymore.

843
00:39:50,755 --> 00:39:54,024
He was sick. He just was
hittin' me and stuff.

844
00:39:54,091 --> 00:39:55,392
No.
Yeah.

845
00:39:55,459 --> 00:39:57,928
He stuck me
with a kitchen knife.

846
00:39:57,995 --> 00:39:59,463
Oh, that's terrible.

847
00:39:59,530 --> 00:40:00,998
Why didn't you tell me?

848
00:40:01,065 --> 00:40:02,366
I was embarrassed.

849
00:40:02,433 --> 00:40:03,834
Aw, ya poor kid.

850
00:40:03,901 --> 00:40:05,803
I figured you'd just say
I deserved it.

851
00:40:05,870 --> 00:40:08,406
Oh, sweetheart, I never would've
said anything like that.

852
00:40:08,472 --> 00:40:12,376
You wouldn't?
No. Nobody deserves that.

853
00:40:12,443 --> 00:40:14,678
[SOBBING]

854
00:40:21,452 --> 00:40:22,920
[SIGHS]

855
00:40:25,456 --> 00:40:28,192
[SNIFFLES]

856
00:40:28,259 --> 00:40:30,494
I have to go to work.

857
00:40:38,435 --> 00:40:40,805
All right, now what?
Any ideas?

858
00:40:40,871 --> 00:40:43,541
Flynn's out, right?
We can't use him now.

859
00:40:43,607 --> 00:40:44,809
No,
of course not.

860
00:40:44,875 --> 00:40:47,011
But where's that
leave us?

861
00:40:47,077 --> 00:40:51,816
Maybe we could get Charlie,
like, ya know, a day pass.

862
00:40:55,219 --> 00:40:57,154
[♪♪♪]

863
00:41:07,464 --> 00:41:09,834
ORDERLY:
Come on. Here we go.

864
00:41:09,900 --> 00:41:11,902
PATIENT:
No, no, no! No, no, no!

865
00:41:18,209 --> 00:41:20,578
[ALL GRUNTING]

866
00:41:24,982 --> 00:41:28,686
SAMMY: Sheesh.
RUDY: Mm-hm.

867
00:41:33,324 --> 00:41:36,126
Nurses!
Rudy!

868
00:41:36,193 --> 00:41:39,797
Listen, honey, we need to take
a patient out for the afternoon.

869
00:41:39,864 --> 00:41:41,832
Uh-huh.
This afternoon?

870
00:41:41,899 --> 00:41:43,567
Yeah, how do we go about
doin' that?

871
00:41:43,634 --> 00:41:45,069
You gotta get
permission.

872
00:41:45,135 --> 00:41:46,637
Well, who do we get
that from?

873
00:41:46,704 --> 00:41:49,139
Doctor.

874
00:41:49,206 --> 00:41:51,275
Which doctor?

875
00:41:51,342 --> 00:41:53,510
The patient's doctor.

876
00:41:53,577 --> 00:41:56,513
Are youse havin' fun with me?
Huh?

877
00:41:56,580 --> 00:41:58,849
'Cause if you're havin' fun
with me,

878
00:41:58,916 --> 00:42:00,985
I'm gonna have fun
with you.

879
00:42:01,051 --> 00:42:03,220
[EXCLAIMS]

880
00:42:03,287 --> 00:42:05,055
[ALL LAUGHING]

881
00:42:05,122 --> 00:42:08,392
Let me see
Charlie Flynn's doctor.

882
00:42:08,459 --> 00:42:11,395
Charles Flynn?

883
00:42:11,462 --> 00:42:13,964
ANGELO:
Yeah, how's he doin'?

884
00:42:14,031 --> 00:42:15,332
How do you mean?

885
00:42:15,399 --> 00:42:17,234
How do I mean?
Ahem.

886
00:42:17,301 --> 00:42:18,769
Yes.

887
00:42:18,836 --> 00:42:22,573
I mean,
is he all right?

888
00:42:22,640 --> 00:42:24,708
[DR. ALSTRICH STAMMERS]

889
00:42:24,775 --> 00:42:28,045
Yes, um, his condition
is improving.

890
00:42:28,112 --> 00:42:30,915
You're from the State Board,
aren't you?

891
00:42:30,981 --> 00:42:33,617
Uh, no.
Oh, yes you are.

892
00:42:33,684 --> 00:42:35,986
No.
Yes, you are.

893
00:42:37,421 --> 00:42:39,156
No.

894
00:42:40,591 --> 00:42:42,293
No.

895
00:42:42,359 --> 00:42:43,527
We're uh, family.

896
00:42:43,594 --> 00:42:45,496
[ALL CHUCKLE]
Oh. Oh, I see.

897
00:42:45,562 --> 00:42:49,133
Is he still violent?

898
00:42:49,199 --> 00:42:50,834
Violent?

899
00:42:52,102 --> 00:42:53,704
Oh, yes.

900
00:42:53,771 --> 00:42:55,039
[ALL SIGH AND EXCLAIM]

901
00:42:55,105 --> 00:42:56,607
JIMMY:
Jeez, that's too bad.

902
00:42:56,674 --> 00:42:59,043
Well, of course,
he's still violent.

903
00:42:59,109 --> 00:43:00,945
What am I expected to do,
work miracles?

904
00:43:01,011 --> 00:43:03,814
Let me tell you something.
I protest.

905
00:43:03,881 --> 00:43:05,883
I protest in the most
vigorous terms,

906
00:43:05,950 --> 00:43:07,985
the Board accusing me--
[NEARBY SCREAMING]

907
00:43:08,052 --> 00:43:09,920
--of, of, of, of,
of incompetence.

908
00:43:09,987 --> 00:43:13,324
They take away my practice,
and-- And then dump me

909
00:43:13,390 --> 00:43:16,894
down here in the midst
of all this...bedlam!

910
00:43:16,961 --> 00:43:19,096
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

911
00:43:23,667 --> 00:43:25,135
What was it you wanted?

912
00:43:25,202 --> 00:43:28,238
Could you let Charlie
out for the day?

913
00:43:28,305 --> 00:43:30,140
What? Oh, no.

914
00:43:30,207 --> 00:43:32,810
No, no, no, no, no, no. That is
completely out of the question.

915
00:43:32,876 --> 00:43:34,712
He's still very, uh,
he's still very violent.

916
00:43:34,778 --> 00:43:37,815
TONY:
Come on, Doc, you said he was
okay. You said he was better.

917
00:43:37,881 --> 00:43:40,050
He's-- He's better than--
Than he was.

918
00:43:40,117 --> 00:43:42,186
Uh, uh, h-he's--
He's coming...

919
00:43:42,252 --> 00:43:45,456
You know, h-h-he's coming along.
Oh, heh.

920
00:43:45,522 --> 00:43:47,057
When he
first arrived here,

921
00:43:47,124 --> 00:43:49,893
he was completely
out of, um,

922
00:43:49,960 --> 00:43:52,596
out of, uh, you know,
out of touch.

923
00:43:52,663 --> 00:43:57,201
But now, after only two weeks
of my-- Of my therapy,

924
00:43:57,267 --> 00:44:02,973
he finally understands that this
is not the thing at all.

925
00:44:03,040 --> 00:44:06,276
But he's still a--
Still a remorseless brute.

926
00:44:06,343 --> 00:44:08,712
But he is tr--
You know, he's trying.

927
00:44:08,779 --> 00:44:10,147
Tryin' what?

928
00:44:10,214 --> 00:44:11,382
Trying to feel.

929
00:44:11,448 --> 00:44:16,520
This man is trying
to cultivate a conscience

930
00:44:16,587 --> 00:44:19,656
like it was a house plant.

931
00:44:19,723 --> 00:44:21,692
Groundbreaking.

932
00:44:21,759 --> 00:44:24,828
And these fucking charlatans
around here

933
00:44:24,895 --> 00:44:27,531
are calling me
a drug-addicted quack.

934
00:44:27,598 --> 00:44:29,566
[PILLS RATTLE]

935
00:44:29,633 --> 00:44:33,037
Let me tell you,
Charles Flynn...

936
00:44:33,103 --> 00:44:36,673
Charles Flynn was--
Let me help you with that.

937
00:44:36,740 --> 00:44:39,676
Oh, boy.

938
00:44:39,743 --> 00:44:42,680
Can we see him?

939
00:44:42,746 --> 00:44:44,882
[♪♪♪]

940
00:44:57,394 --> 00:44:59,363
[HUMMING]

941
00:45:03,000 --> 00:45:05,135
[DISTANT SCREAMING]

942
00:45:08,472 --> 00:45:10,474
Hello, Charlie.

943
00:45:10,541 --> 00:45:12,009
Hello.

944
00:45:12,076 --> 00:45:15,379
How ya been?
How have I been?

945
00:45:15,446 --> 00:45:17,181
Pft, how have I been?

946
00:45:17,247 --> 00:45:19,983
How the hell does it look
like I've been?

947
00:45:20,050 --> 00:45:21,385
You look good.
Don't he look good?

948
00:45:21,452 --> 00:45:23,220
You look great.
Yeah, he looks good.

949
00:45:23,287 --> 00:45:25,889
It's a nice room, Charlie.
Yeah.

950
00:45:25,956 --> 00:45:27,157
Yeah, yeah, real nice.

951
00:45:27,224 --> 00:45:29,359
What do you got,
a north view here?

952
00:45:29,426 --> 00:45:31,028
I don't know.

953
00:45:31,095 --> 00:45:34,698
Charlie, we got a job.
You want it?

954
00:45:34,765 --> 00:45:36,600
I can't
leave the hospital.

955
00:45:36,667 --> 00:45:39,103
Well, I don't see no
lock-up here.

956
00:45:39,169 --> 00:45:43,540
If I leave the hospital,
I-I can go to jail.

957
00:45:43,607 --> 00:45:47,111
Uh, we'll cover for ya.
It'll just take a couple hours.

958
00:45:47,177 --> 00:45:49,046
Interested?

959
00:45:49,113 --> 00:45:50,914
You got a cigarette?

960
00:45:50,981 --> 00:45:52,216
Oh, sure.

961
00:45:52,282 --> 00:45:54,718
Sammy, give him a smoke.
Oh, yeah.

962
00:45:54,785 --> 00:45:56,954
[DISTANT CACKLING]

963
00:45:58,088 --> 00:45:59,790
Give him
the whole pack.

964
00:45:59,857 --> 00:46:01,658
It's my only one.

965
00:46:01,725 --> 00:46:03,260
All right.

966
00:46:07,531 --> 00:46:09,566
Are these French?
Huh?

967
00:46:09,633 --> 00:46:12,002
No.

968
00:46:12,069 --> 00:46:13,637
Aah!

969
00:46:13,704 --> 00:46:15,939
They look French.

970
00:46:16,006 --> 00:46:18,008
Uh, no, they're--
They're American cigarettes.

971
00:46:18,075 --> 00:46:21,044
They're like, uh,
they're like menthol.

972
00:46:21,111 --> 00:46:23,447
They're just regular
American cigarettes.

973
00:46:23,514 --> 00:46:26,683
CHARLIE:
They better not be French.

974
00:46:26,750 --> 00:46:28,152
[SAMMY WHIMPERS]

975
00:46:28,218 --> 00:46:30,754
Gimme a light.
What?

976
00:46:30,821 --> 00:46:33,423
[DISTANT YELLING]

977
00:46:36,627 --> 00:46:38,529
How much?

978
00:46:38,595 --> 00:46:40,597
The usual.

979
00:46:46,303 --> 00:46:47,938
I want more.

980
00:46:48,005 --> 00:46:51,141
ANGELO:
We'll work it out.

981
00:46:51,208 --> 00:46:53,944
[SIZZLES]
[SCREAMS]

982
00:46:54,011 --> 00:46:55,179
CHARLIE:
Oh, that's nice.

983
00:46:55,245 --> 00:46:57,381
SAMMY:
